<DESCRIPT>  MIAMI; NEW-YORK; PROFESSIONAL; FOOTBALL; PLAYOFF; GAME  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Kickoff: 9:30 a.m., Rich Stadium, Orchard Park, N.Y.; Line: Buffalo is favored
by 7 points.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  MIAMI VS. BUFFALO  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  NFL Playoffs;  Today's TV Matchup  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  Television/radio: 3 4 8 /KCBS (740).; Records: Miami finished the regular
season 12-4 and in second place in the AFC East. The Dolphins are a wild-card
team. Buffalo finished 13-3 and won the division title.; Series: Miami leads
the regular-season series 35-14-1. This is the teams' third meeting this
season. Miami won the first game 30-7 and Buffalo the second 24-14. This is
the teams' first playoff meeting.; Dolphins update: Miami beat Kansas City
17-16 in the AFC wild-card game last Saturday. QB Dan Marino rallied the
Dolphins in the fourth quarter, completing all eight of his passes, including
two for touchdowns, as Miami overcame a 16-3 deficit. The Dolphins have lost
four straight at Buffalo. Miami's defense allowed 242 points during the
season, the second-lowest total in the AFC.; Bills update: This is Buffalo's
playoff opener. The Bills' chances of winning might depend on whether injured
QB Jim Kelly plays. Kelly, who practiced Tuesday for the first time since
sustaining cartilage and ligament damage to his left knee Dec. 15 against the
New York Giants, said he'll decide today whether he can play. Frank Reich is
expected to start at QB. In Buffalo's 24-14 win Dec. 23, Reich completed 15 of
21 passes for 234 yards and two TDs. Buffalo led the NFL in scoring with 428
points. RB Thurman Thomas led the league in yards from scrimmage (1,829).; Key
injuries: Miami -- LB John Offerdahl (foot), NT Shawn Lee (back), NT Alfred
Oglesby (groin), CB Tim McKyer (heel) are questionable. Buffalo -- QB Kelly
(knee), DE Leon Seals (knee) are questionable. LB Ray Bentley (chest) is
probable.  </TEXT>
